      "snowpackStructure": {
        "comment": "On Saturday it will be very mild over a wide area. <br/> <br/> Shady slopes: The snowpack remains prone to triggering in some places. Distinct weak layers exist in the old snowpack in particular on west, north and east facing slopes. <br/> <br/> Outgoing longwave radiation during the night will be good. The surface of the snowpack will freeze to form a strong crust and will soften during the day. Sunshine and high temperatures will give rise as the day progresses to thorough wetting of the snowpack in particular on steep sunny slopes below approximately 2600 m. This also applies at the base of rock walls."
      },
      "source": {
